v_categories_description_1:
Bike Filters

The knowledge and experience gained on track is transferred to street production in order to offer performance products, tested and in continuous evolution, designed to satisfy the requirements of the most demanding motorcyclists. The materials used in production are of the highest standard: filters are made in one single piece with no welded joints thus avoiding breakage; the filtering material is composed of a special cotton gauze soaked with low viscosity oil and covered with an epoxy coated alloy mesh to ensure protection from petrol fumes and oxidization due to air humidity. Furthermore the cotton has the advantage of being washable and therefore reusable. In this way BMC air filters guarantee superior air capacity in respect to traditional paper filters enabling minimum loss of power in the air flow and therefore obtaining better performance from the engine.

v_categories_description_1:
Buy from the experts

When you buy Final Inspection products through Tigersoft Performance, you are not simply buying from another retailer. We use these products every day detailing the cars of our customers to perfection, we know them inside and out. And so when you buy through us, you also get expert advise from professionals that actually use the products they are selling.

All prices are fully inclusive

All of the prices of BC Forged Wheels on this website are fully inclusive.

That means that all Shipping Charges, Insurance, Customs Import Duty and GST are all included in the price, there is absolutely nothing else to pay!

And when we say that shipping is included, we mean right to your front door.

Find Out More

If you would like to learn about:

  • Cast vs Forged Wheels
  • Why Weight is so important
  • How BC Forged Wheels are made

Then please visit

BC Forged Wheels Info

Custom Made to Order

All BC Forged Wheels are custom-made to your specifications.

You specify all dimensions and options for your wheels, and then once your order is placed, your wheels will be on your doorstep within 30 days!

Many Styles and Colours

Each Series presented below has a range of styles available, not just the style shown in the picture

Each style of wheel has a wide range of colour and finishing options available

v_categories_description_1:
Martini Grand Prix Lubricant Range

Martini Racing Products Produces a huge range of conventional service lubricants . These are made to very high quality standards but are made available at a very attractive price point when compared to "brand name" service lubricant manufacturers.

Martini Synthetic Engine Lubricant Range

Martini Racing Products manufactures a complete range of synthetic engine oils for a variety of applications in line with our "Competition Fluids Management Program"

All our Motor oils now have the added benefits of " Superlube" technology built into every drop of our product.

Backed up by dyno results and championship trophies, Martini Racing Synthetic Engine Oils are market leaders in the horsepower and reliability stakes. These qualities are reflected in track results and season reliability records re-set time again and again when using our range of products.
